^nC_k\text{ } ^nC_r = ^nC_r\text{ }^{n-r}C_{k-r}
0\le r\le k\le n
\binom{n}{k} \binom{k}{r}
k
n
r
k
\binom{n}{k} \binom{k}{r} = \frac{n!}{k!(n-k)!} \frac{k!}{r!(k-r)!} = \frac{n!}{(n-k)!r!(k-r)!}
\binom{n}{r} \binom{n-r}{k-r} = \frac{n!}{r!(n-r)!} \frac{(n-r)!}{(k-r)!((n-r)-(k-r))!} = \frac{n!}{r!(k-r)!(n-k)!}.
